reviewText: The Winans always,always sing there best so just like M.C.Hammer says CAN'T TOUCH THIS so this was a gift that I gave my MOM because she never really seen them perform.

I rate this product a three because of the grainy quality of the product when viewing.  As far as delivery and the conditions of the dvd when delivered, I say it was fine.  Tightly wrapped and delivered in a very timely manner, the seller was superb in handling the process.  I only wished I had enjoyed what I ordered.

I love the Winans which is why it kills me to have to give this DVD such a low rating (as I expected more).  Didn't live up to my expectations...which is truly sad :(

Rick
I only enjoyed 4 out of the 16 performances..."Goodness, Mercy and Grace", "Question Is" - MY FAVORITE!, "If I Labor", and "Restoration". I don't advise ANYONE to pay over $10 for this dvd.
I love this DVD the performances are genuine and moving. It is nice to have a DVD of gospel performers in the early days it is so real and down to earth.
This is the only live performance available of the Winans, therefore I consider it to be a collector's item. The video and sound quality are both subpar but, with it is still a rare gem.

I enjoy the Winans very much, this DVD I did not enjoy, and is more of a home video that maybe the Winans would enjoy of their early days. If I'd had a chance to preview this DVD I would not have purchased it.  THANK YOU

I have seen this video once before.  My sister and I rented it from a video store. I was thinking Oh! this video is one of their old videos it probably want be all that good.  but as we begin to watch it.  From the beginning the power of God was all over this video.  It's a must see video for anyone.
A must see ... Winans when best!
I LIKE THE WINANS AND THEIR MUSIC
Great music. Grand concert on DVD.
ANNOINTED, RIP....POP WINANS, RONALD WINANS
Disappointed with dvd
satisfied
Works great shipped on time
Love, love, love this group, I bought the cassettes when they first came out and somehow lost track, it is great to have these wonderful songs so full of experience, God's love and fond remembrances

I read reviews on the quality but it's even worse than you'd think. Kudos to the person who captured the moment but it should've been kept as a personal memory & should never have been duplicated & sold.
SUPERB CONCERT
I love the Winans  but the production quality and hearing the audio awful. Realizing that this is an older DVD it still should be better quality.
Good music for the soul. Thank you.
It wasn't what i expected
Excellent
ok

Classic  DVD, glad I made the investment it's a must have for gospel music lovers collection! This DVD also included Fred Hammond in his early day s & Commission as well as other Detroit music legends. Thanks

I'm very satisfied with the DVD, I didn't expect anything more than what I received, except I thought it was only their family, so that was a plus to see alot of other artists included. Thanks and Be Blessed.
Did not care for this dvd at all.  The quality of the recording is very poor visually as well as the sound.
I bought this for my mom for Christmas.  According to her the whole dvd consisted of the lady Vicki that was supposedly hosting. When it says Winans. That's who we expect to see. Complete waste!!!

I THOUGHT THIS VIDEO WOULD BE GREAT. BUT IT WASN'T. THE AUDIENCE WAS HO-HUM AND IT JUST DIDN'T GIVE ME THE UMPH! I WON'T WATCH IT AGAIN. IT WAS MORE THE AUDIENCE THAN THE PERFORMANCES OF THE SINGERS. THEY DID AN AWESOME JOB BUT THE AUDIENCE JUST KILLS IT FOR YOU WATCHING THEM JUST SIT THERE AND ACT LIKE NO ONE IS ON STAGE GIVING THEIR ALL.
I always loved the Winans, & this dvd is a must have for the gospel music lover. 2 Thumbs up.
Awesome DVD
I always enjoy the Winans.  The 4 brothers that started it all.

This DVD is own by Xenon pictures the people that are behind racist gangster movies like welcome to Deathrow and coonskin. They are not friendly people, they are just looking to make a quick dollar off of gospel artist none of the money goes to the gospel singers on this dvd.
Fabulous

I love this DVD. The music is still relevant today. The actual quality of the recording is not extremely professional, but the singing is great.

I enjoyed these songs while I was growing up. We sang them in the choir as well as we grew older. I used to sing the "La la La song to my daughter when she was born.... now she is two years old and can sing it on her own. Most nights we sing together before bed and she calls it her song.... Mummy please sing Peaches' song..
